<HEADLINE>
Blair "delighted" that Charles and Camilla to wed
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prime Minister Tony Blair on Thursday congratulated Prince Charles and Camilla
Parker Bowles after the heir to the throne announced he will marry his long-time
partner.
</P>
<P>
"I'm delighted for the Prince of Wales and Camilla Parker Bowles," Blair said in
a statement broadcast on British TV.
</P>
<P>
"It's very happy news and when the Cabinet heard it this morning they sent their
congratulations and good wishes on behalf of the whole government," the prime
minister added.
</P>
<P>
"We all wish them every happiness for their future together."
</P>
</TEXT>
